<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-22T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-22T23:00:00-05:00" n="698" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d698">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3–2349: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-23T12:00:00+08:00">March 23,
                                1949—noon.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received March 23—3:54 a. m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>629. New Premier<note n="33" xml:id="d698fn33">General Ho Ying-chin.</note>
                        came to see me Sunday evening to discuss chaotic financial situation and its
                        mortal threat to his Cabinet in the making. He requested US support for
                        Chinese currency, suggesting a kind of stabilizing loan of “2 or 300 million
                        dollars”. He said that unless support in some degree were forthcoming from
                        abroad promptly, new government if formed could not survive nor could it be
                        expected to hold its own in any peace talks with Communists. I made no
                        comment other than that I would transmit his request to my Government. Our
                        comments follow separately.<note n="34" xml:id="d698fn34">
                            <hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi>
                        </note>
                    </p>
                    <p>Sent Department, repeated Canton 182, Shanghai 288.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>